==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moisture
<hw>Mois"ture</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>moistour</ets>, F. <ets>moiteur</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
moderate degree of wetness.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which moistens or makes damp or wet; exuding
fluid; liquid in small quantity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All my body's <qex>moisture</qex>⟦br⟧
Scarce serves to quench my furnace-burning heat.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moistureless</ent>⟦br⟧
